Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Customs officials at Beirut International Airport 
yesterday thwarted an attempt to smuggle 4.5 kg of cocaine into 
Lebanon. Smuggler Jean Halim Khalifah, from al-Hadath, was 
arrested as he arrived from Brazil. Khalifah hid the drugs in 
small nylon bags. He was detained and referred to the 
Counternarcotics Bureau for interrogation. 

